extends layout.pug

block content
  main.text-content
    h2 Migrate your Fusion Table Maps

    p
      | The Fusion Tables Archive Tool is an easy way to preserve existing maps generated with Google Fusion Tables. Built by Google and&thinsp;
      a(href="https://ubilabs.net/en", title="Ubilabs") Ubilabs
      | &thinsp;as an&thinsp;
      a(href="https://github.com/google/fusion-tables-archive-visualizer", title="Fusion Tables Archive Visualizer on Github") open source project
      | , the tool aims to preserve your data and migrate your maps before the&thinsp;
      a(href="https://support.google.com/fusiontables/answer/9185417", title="Notice: Google Fusion Tables Turndown") Fusion Tables shutdown
      | &thinsp;on December 3, 2019. You have access to the exporting portion of this tool until the shutdown date. If you only want to save your Fusion Tables data as CSV & KML files, and don't need the maps, then consider using&thinsp;
      a(href="https://takeout.google.com/", title="Google Takeout") Google Takeout
      | &thinsp;instead.

    p
      | This tool will export each selected Fusion Table to its own spreadsheet or CSV file “archive” in your Google Drive, and will generate a Google map based on the archive. This tool tries to preserve your map styling and basic balloon templates. Your archives are saved in a folder called “ft-archive”.  Links to your archives and maps are listed in a Google Sheet called “ft-archive-index”.

    p
      | To get started, sign in with your Google account below. This tool uses the following access rights or "scopes" (see&thinsp;
      a(href="https://developers.google.com/drive/api/v2/about-auth", title="Authorizing requests with OAuth 2.0") here
      | &thinsp;for more information on scopes):

    ul
      li Read your tables (fusiontables.readonly)
      li List the tables that you own (drive.metadata.readonly)
      li Create and update the necessary folders, spreadsheets and files in Google drive (drive.file)

    p
      | This site uses cookies to provide access rights to Google services (Fusion Tables and Drive). The cookies are discarded when you leave this site. No information from this site is shared with anyone else. By signing in below, you consent to our use of cookies.

    p
      | If you have more questions about the tool or the archives, please&thinsp;
      a(href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TrKT9FS3IryH6ahAfYX_7joMtiIq_p_vPCQ-lYyktm0/edit?usp=sharing", title="Fusion Tables Export FAQ") read this FAQ
      | .

